By Emmanuel Antswen The Police in Benue have confirmed attacks by some gunmen on communities in Gwer West Local Government Area of the state. The Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) in the state, Catherine Anene, confirmed the attack on Monday to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN). The police spokesperson said the command was yet to receive full details of the incident. Anene said that gunmen in the early hours of Monday attacked Mbamondu and Vengav, in Avihijime council ward in Udam and Tse Amgbem close to Aondona, all in Gwer West Local Government. She, however, said that the Command was also yet to get full details of the attack on the communities. (NAN) Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Like this:Like Loading... Like Loading...  	Related Unknown gunmen kill 3 police officers in Benue – PPROThe Benue Police Command say unknown gunmen killed three Police officers at the residence of the Katsina-Ala LGA Chairman Mr Alfred Atera.December 24, 2020In "Defence/Security"Gunmen attack Ebonyi communityThe Commissioner of Police in Ebonyi, Aliyu Garba, confirmed on Monday that gunmen attacked another community in the state.April 12, 2021In "General News"Police deploy 5,200 personnel for LG polls in BenueBy Emmanuel Antswen The Police Command in Benue said it had deployed 5,200 personnel for Saturday, May 30 Local Government Elections in the state. DSP Catherine Anene, the State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), told News Agency of Nigeira (NAN) that the personnel were also drawn from sister agencies. Anene…May 30, 2020In "Defence/Security" Unknown gunmen kill 3 police officers in Benue – PPROThe Benue Police Command say unknown gunmen killed three Police officers at the res